```
{
  "data": {
    "story": {
      "link_data": {
        "link": "https://example.com",
        "message": "The main body of the post, above the image.",
        "picture": "https://example.com/ad-picture.png",
        "description": "Link description below the image's title.",
        "call_to_action": {
          "type": "OPEN_LINK",
          "value": {
            "link_caption": "example.com/subscribe"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

These are the keys you have to provide, as shown in the example.

- `story.link_data.link` (string): the URL the user will be redirected to when
clicking the ad.
- `story.link_data.message` (string): the main body of the post, above the image.
- `story.link_data.picture` (string): URL of the ad image.
- `story.link_data.description` (string): text that appears below the ad image.
- `story.link_data.call_to_action.type` (string): one of the values defined
in [this page](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/marketing-api/reference/ad-creative-link-data-call-to-action/). Use `OPEN_LINK` for generic ads that take users
to other pages.
- `story.link_data.call_to_action.value.link_caption` (string): This is the
URL that will show up to the user.
This has to be similar to `story.link_data.link`.

